* f9dasm control file for HP 1630/1631A kernel ROM B0061 (01630-80061, chip7/U4H)
* Disassembled at base $C000 (file off X -> logical $C000+X); resident kernel = $F000-$FFFF.
* Entry spine = main_entry $F089 (called at end of init_hw); plus reset + IRQ vectors.
* Labels/comments from emulation-driven RE (see ../annotations/B0061_labels.txt, ../RE_NOTES.md).

* ---- direct page (kernel runs with DP=0) ----
setdp C000-FFFF 00

* ---- entry vectors (flow-followed) ----
* known sub-entries (reached via indirect/computed calls)

* ---- labels ----
label F089 main_entry
label FD80 RESET
label FDC8 init_hw
label FEB4 init_tail
label FEB9 struct_clear
label F31F init_sub_F31F
label F37B post_ramtest
label F412 post_romchecksum
label F3E4 romchk_bankloop
label F420 romchk_compare
label F441 post_clear_A
label F451 post_clear_B
label F45B display_init
label F4A9 disp_vsync_test
label F4B7 disp_init_cont
label F500 selftest_orch
label F530 display_hex_byte
label F54F display_string
label F600 setup_operational_map
label F637 mmu_set_page
label F664 clear_mem
label F6C3 pre_reset_sub
label F6C4 selftest_result_disp
label F6FA vsync_wait
label F701 post_delay
label F70F reboot
label F084 isr_swi
label FADB isr_irq
label FBBD isr_nmi
label FBA3 isr_firq

* ---- data regions ----
word FD88-FDC7   * mmu_boot_table: 32x16b page-map (copied to $FF00)
data F07C-F083   * romchk_expected_tbl: 8 per-bank checksum bytes
data F66F-F6B1   * self-test result strings/tables
fcc  F6B2-F6C2   * "SELF TEST PASSED" (00-terminated)
word FFF0-FFFF   * 6809 vector table (reserved,SWI3,SWI2,FIRQ,IRQ,SWI,NMI,RESET)
label FFFE vec_RESET
label FFFC vec_NMI
label FFF8 vec_IRQ
label FFF6 vec_FIRQ

* ---- explanatory line comments ----
lcomment F089 main_entry: top of the application/dispatch (boot flows here from init_hw)
lcomment FDC8 init_hw: mask ints, copy 64B MMU map FD88->$FF00, init CRTC/8279, LDS #$E1FD
lcomment FD88 initial MMU page map (32 x 16-bit: attr<<8 | phys 2KB-page)
lcomment F37B POST RAM test: walk DRAM phys pages $280-$29F via reg0, walking-bit pattern
lcomment F412 POST ROM checksum: sum logical $0000-$3FFF per bank, CMPA vs $F07C table
lcomment F45B program MC6845 CRTC ($E032-$E038) + 8279 ($E848-$E84F)
lcomment F4A9 read $E852 bit2 (CRT vsync: 1=active) to gate display init
lcomment F600 reprogram MMU into operational map (kernel low, overlays $6000-$BFFF)
lcomment F637 mmu_set_page: write $FF00-region page registers (A=logical page, X=phys)
lcomment F6C4 copy SELF-TEST result strings into CRT RAM $D00E/$D012 (row stride $17)
lcomment F6FA spin while $E852 bit2 set (wait CRT retrace)
lcomment F70F JMP [$FFFE]: re-enter RESET (self-test loops; unconditional)
